Catzavelos wants crimen injuria charges against him dropped. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The EFF says it’s confident Adam Catzavelos will stand trial for the use of the k-word in a viral video. This as Catzavelos is continuing his fight to get a charge of crimen injuria against him dropped. READ: EFF releases SARS 'rogue unit' report The Randburg Magistrates Court heard that his legal team is still waiting for a decision from the national director of public prosecutions – on whether the case will be dropped. Representations to the Gauteng office have already been unsuccessful – while the way forward in the Greek prosecution remains unclear. READ: Malema rejects Zille's invite to tea Catzavelos caused an uproar in 2018 after a video emerged of him using the k-word while on holiday in Greece.